The case of a 24-year-old woman, who is accused of abducting a newborn baby from Chris Hani Baragwanath Hospital in Soweto in June, has been postponed for further investigation. Kereleng Ramoisa briefly appeared in the Protea Magistrate's Court on Monday when the case was postponed. The newborn baby was abducted on June 6 at the hospital's maternity ward by a woman who claimed to be a family member. Police viewed CCTV footage which showedÂ a woman roaming around the antenatal clinic before leaving the maternity area carrying a baby in a purple blanket. WATCH: Hundreds of hospital beds 'dumped' outside Baragwanath A video gone viral on social media shows hundreds of hospital beds stacked outside Chris Hani Baragwanath hospital in Johannesburg. She asked to take the baby outside to show family members, but never returned, News24 earlier reported. The surveillance also revealed that there were two accomplices were with her. ALSO READ | Abducted Baragwanath hospital newborn 'sold for R2 500' - report Ramoisa was allegedly found with the baby in Diepkloof, Soweto, 24 hours after the child was taken from the hospital. ALSO READ | PIC: Alleged accomplice of woman who abducted newborn baby at hospital detained The motive for the abduction is unknown. She is out on bail and is expected to appear in court again on August 28.  GET THE NEWS at your fingertips and download the News24 app for Android here now. Get it for your iPhone here. KEEP UPDATED on the latest news by subscribing to our FREE newsletter. - FOLLOW News24 on Twitter